lanta georgia us key people rex d adams chairman martin l flanagan ceo phil taylor sr director mark armour sr director wilbur ross ceo wl ross products investment management real estate distressed investing bank loans quantitative equity fundamental equity fixed income hedge funds fund of funds environmental investing and etfs revenue us  million   us  million   operating income us  million   us  million   net income us  million   us  million   total assets us  million   us  million   total equity us  million   us  million   number of employees   website wwwinvescocom invesco ltd is an american independent investment management company that is headquartered in atlanta georgia united states and has branch offices in  countries its common stock is a constituent of the sp  and trades on the new york stock exchange invesco operates under the invesco trimark invesco perpetual wl ross and powershares brand names contents  history  key financial statistics  see also  references  external links historyedit invesco headquarters in atlanta georgia invesco all caps was created in atlanta in  when citizens  southern national bank divested its money management operations in  the company was purchased by the british firm britannia arrow based in london which later took the invesco name in  invesco plc merged with aim investments upon completion of the merger the company adopted the name amvescap since  invesco has grown through acquisitions such as the etf firm powershares capital management and the restructuring of wl ross  co in  the company agreed to a  million settlement with the attorneys general of new york colorado and the sec after allegations of improper trading practices in may  the company changed their name to invesco initial cap only plc moved its primary stock market listing from the london stock exchange to the nyse and became domiciled in bermuda adopting the name invesco ltd as a result the companys shares were withdrawn from the ftse  index and added to the russell  index in november  invesco moved its headquarters from london to atlanta invesco plans to list the powershares global progressive transportation portfolio ptrp on the nasdaq stock market on october   invesco bought morgan stanleys retail unit including van kampen investments for  billion in april  invesco aim became invesco later that year it was reported that invesco had plans to introduce a risk parity commodity fund according to regulatory filings in december  invesco reported assets under management aum of  billion key financial statisticsedit year ending operating revenue net income assets under management employees  december   million  million  billion   december   million  million  billion   december   million  million  billion   december   million  million  billion  see alsoedit invesco perpetual referencesedit  a b c d e f g invesco ltd  annual report form k xbrl united states securities and exchange commission february     invesco ltd  q quarterly report form q xbrl united states securities and exchange commission may     a b invesco ltd  q quarterly report form q xbrl united states securities and exchange commission may     annual report  pdf invesco retrieved    company overview invesco retrieved    a b karkaria urvaksh  invesco moving global hq to atlanta atlanta business chronicle retrieved    chernoff joel  invescos uk business hit hard pensions  investments retrieved    a b company history invesco retrieved    wyatt edward  invesco to acquire aim for  billion the new york times issn  retrieved    timmons heather  september   fund groups to pay  million to end inquiry the new york times retrieved    invesco plc shareholders approve relisting on the new york stock exchange pdf press release invesco  november  retrieved    lse to replace invesco in uks ftse  reuters  november  retrieved    invesco powershares to list global progressive transportation etf pdf retrieved    green transportation fund set to launch retrieved    invesco pulls the trigger